thread.title: Wetherspoon has an unexpected celebrity fan

author: Neil Shaw
title: Wetherspoon has an unexpected celebrity fan
text:
News Wetherspoon has an unexpected celebrity fan "The food is good, it's good value and it's owner backs Brexit - what more could one hope for?" Posh Tory MP Jacob Rees-Mogg is a secret fan of Wetherspoons pubs, he has revealed.
The leading Brexiteer says he frequently visits the chain's branches for their "good English food at good value".
He spoke at the opening of a new branch in his constituency at Midsomer Norton, Somerset, on Friday where he was guest of the founder Tim Martin. Read More Wetherspoon boss ridiculed for fashion faux pas on Good Morning Britain
Mr Martin is a vocal supporter of Brexit and tax equality on food and drink.
Asked if he visits Wetherspoon pubs, Mr Rees-Mogg said: "I have been a lot, I like good English food at good value.
"I went into the kitchen and the staff there are incredibly efficient, the food is good, it's good value and it's owner backs Brexit - what more could one hope for?" Like us on Facebook
